The correct way to circumvent this is using [Window.postMessage](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/postMessage) - Essentially, send a message from the iframe up to its parent window, which, if it has an event listener for `&quot;message&quot;`, can react accordingly.

ie.:

**`a.com/index.html`**
```html
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;script&gt;
      var someFunc = t =&gt; document.querySelector(&quot;#test&quot;).text = t;
      window.addEventListener(&quot;message&quot;, e =&gt; {
        if (e.data === &quot;Changed text&quot;) someFunc(e.data);
      });
    &lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;span id=&quot;test&quot;&gt;This is some dummy text.&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;iframe src=&quot;https://b.com/index.html&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
```

**`b.com/index.html`**
```html
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;button id=&quot;btn&quot;&gt;Test&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;script&gt;
      document.querySelector(&quot;#btn&quot;).addEventListener(&quot;click&quot;, (e) =&gt; {
        window.parent.postMessage(&quot;Changed text&quot;, &quot;http://a.com&quot;);
      });
    &lt;/script&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
```

